To use:

* Setup a Linode account and get an API key: https://www.linode.com/docs/platform/api/api-key

* Clone ceph-ansible: https://github.com/ceph/ceph-ansible.git

* install python virtualenv package (exact package name may vary) unless you are using python3

* Setup a virtualenv with linode-python:

    $ virtualenv linode-env && source linode-env/bin/activate && pip install linode-python

* Modify cluster.json to have the desired count and Linode plan for each daemon type.  cluster.json.sample is provided as an example.

* Edit linode.yml to define ceph-ansible vars. See: https://github.com/ceph/ceph-ansible/wiki#common

* Start using:

    $ LINODE_API_KEY=ABC...DEF ./launch.sh --ceph-ansible /path/to/ceph-ansible
